<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-06-22T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-06-22T04:00:00-05:00" n="463" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d463">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M) Portugal/1128:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Fish</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-22T11:00:00+02:00">June 22,
                                    1943—11 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received June 22—10:04 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1372. Legation’s 1303, June 12, 6 p.m. Notes have been exchanged
                            extending the wolfram agreement from March 1 to June 30, 1943, with
                            clause (G) modified by the raising of the Anglo-American off-take from
                            the pool to 50 percent. Copies by pouch.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to London and Madrid.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Fish</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>